SUMMARY:Validate Yourself to End the Crippling Hurt of Self-Judgments 
DESCRIPTION:Raleigh & Triangle Activities Meetup Group\nDid you know that 
 as a divine creator consciousness\, you have all the power you’ll ever n
 eed to make all your dreams come true? Yes\, unlimited health\, wealth\, l
 ove and happiness forever. And not just someday if you work smart and hard
  enough\, but easily smoothly starting now because you’re always good en
 ough. Sounds like fantasy? Well that’s just the sad cynical state of the
  world today. But exceptional people show what’s possible\, and your hop
 es and dreams live on with the best moments of your own gratitude. Join us
  Sunday April 5\, 2026 for a free empowering talk on how to finally bridge
  the gap between the old hurt past and the heartfelt future ideal. The key
  will be the mastery of judgments\, something that the Easter guy told us 
 to watch out for.\n\nIt’s Easter Sunday\, and whatever you think of the 
 Jesus story\, the ideas are fascinating. To be clear\, we’re talking abo
 ut the radical teacher of peace and forgiveness who so completely practice
 d non-violence that he allowed himself to be killed just to then - as the 
 story goes - resurrect on Easter Sunday to prove nothing’s impossible fo
 r love. We’re definitely not talking about the perversely distorted warr
 ior Jesus that some apocalyptic Christians claim to serve by starting Worl
 d War 3. More than ever\, we need world-healing truths like Jesus truly ta
 ught\, aka Jeshua. Do unto others as you would have them do unto you. Love
  your neighbor as yourself. Be like little children if you want to enter t
 he kingdom of heaven. The meek shall inherit the Earth. And “Judge not l
 est ye be judged.” Say what?\n\nNegative judgments are the little attack
 ing opinions we inflict on ourselves and each other\, all day long\, often
  without thinking. “That’s bad\, you shouldn’t do that\, you’re wr
 ong\, that’s stupid\, how selfish\, how could you.” Such statements ar
 e unbelievably common in our culture\, and yet Jesus said to stop. Why? We
 ’ve been socially trained to think that disapproval is the basis of moti
 vating change. If people aren’t guided by some sort of criticism or thre
 at\, it’s just assumed they’ll become lazy\, self-serving and destruct
 ive. Look at all the compulsive addictive escapist behaviors ruining our l
 ives. Shape up\, try harder\, do better! And all the awful greedy cruel pe
 ople destroying the world today. They need more judgments to make them sto
 p\, right?\n\nActually judgments ARE the problem\, and 2000 years after Je
 sus was killed for trying to explain\, we’re all gonna die if we don’t
  understand. Don’t worry\, that’s not a judgment or a threat\, it’s 
 just an observation. The alternative to negative judging will come easily 
 enough for anyone who cares. And the uncaring people will become irrelevan
 t by law of attraction. Incompatible vibrations become invisible to each o
 ther in the multiverse. Spirits are just people in parallel realities\, ca
 lling us to join them in heavens on the Earth. The belief systems that col
 lapse the quantum wave functions can be consciously chosen to receive what
  he called eternal life. Jesus didn’t have all the vocabulary that we ha
 ve today. But he did say greater things than he did we will do.\n\nBasical
 ly\, negative judgments are the sign of negative false belief systems that
  scare us into thinking that people are bad and life is dangerous so every
 thing must be controlled. Actually\, life is completely safe and people ar
 e naturally good. We must stop judging ourselves so divine nature can take
  its course. Everything will heal very quickly\, to the point of people wo
 rking with higher consciousness and nature spirits to restore the planet t
 o eternal life and joy as the system was designed to function. If my visio
 ns sound like childish fantasy\, that’s a sign of how much we need spiri
 tual re-education. Life is good\, and violence is the paranoid fantasy tha
 t can be dropped without negatively judging.\n\nWhat self-judgments do you
  suffer\, that get you down and make you hopeless to live your happy desti
 ny? Have you had moments of clarity when the negative thinking stopped\, p
 erhaps by meditation\, mindfulness\, or mystical experience? From my own s
 tudies\, I’ll share secrets of self-validation that end the patterns of 
 crippling self-judgments. We’ll look at negative versus positive judging
 \, how reality is created from our own energy so judgments only hurt the s
 elf\, and how the negative ego (aka devil) is laid to rest with self-forgi
 veness in the spiritual human state of “Christ consciousness”. Physica
 l reality is a projection from our Spirit Home\, so with self-validation w
 e reconnect with Source to be guided where we belong to thrive.\n\nWelcome
 ! Our Inner Selves Mastery spiritual support group is free online every Su
 nday 11am-130pm EDT\, with the last 30 minutes for a guided meditation. If
  you can’t stay you can get the recording. You can signup here for this 
 meeting and visit www.signupISM.com for all events\, newsletter\, videos\,
  and more.\n\nBest wishes\,\nCarl Johann Schroeder\nInner Selves Mastery\n
 spiritual teaching and coaching\nquick-links at [www.signupISM.com](http:/
 /www.signupISM.com)
